1
00:00:03,560 --> 00:00:06,420
What is the most important thing in pursuing a girl?

2
00:00:08,640 --> 00:00:09,880
Romance.

3
00:00:14,520 --> 00:00:15,560
Romance.

4
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,680
You two,

5
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:27,560
that was my limited-edition eyebrow pencil.

6
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:28,760
It's one thing for you two to share one,

7
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:29,960
but using two of mine?

8
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:31,640
Are you even human?

9
00:01:34,039 --> 00:01:36,200
Doesn't your pencil have two colors?

10
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:37,200
Besides,

11
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:39,720
abs need shadows to look real.

12
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:40,840
Real, my foot.

13
00:01:41,320 --> 00:01:42,759
I'm almost blind.

14
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:44,600
What kind of macho show was that?

15
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:46,530
How could you two come up with that?

16
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:47,960
We thought

17
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:50,360
you girls like macho men.

18
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:52,479
We practiced in front of the poster for a whole day.

19
00:01:52,479 --> 00:01:53,080
Yeah.

20
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:56,720
Even if we like macho men,

21
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,600
what about romance?

22
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:00,280
Where is the romance?

23
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:01,920
Right,

24
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:03,120
where's the romance?

25
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,240
Why are you asking me?

26
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:05,400
Wasn't it your idea?

27
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,440
It doesn't matter whose idea it was.

28
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:09,440
What matters is what we do next.

29
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:11,200
Here are your baked eggs.

30
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:12,120
Okay, thanks.

31
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:14,560
You two idiots.

32
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:15,760
Eat your eggs.

33
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:16,640
Eat.

34
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:17,300
All for you.

35
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:29,120
There are so many romantic things in the world.

36
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:31,320
Why is it so difficult for you two?

37
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:33,120
Hey, look.

38
00:02:33,640 --> 00:02:36,840
I think the song dedication back there is quite romantic.

39
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:37,600
That works.

40
00:02:37,880 --> 00:02:38,880
It's simple, too.

41
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:39,800
Forget it.

42
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:41,760
There's already a Zhang Zhiwei.

43
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,500
If Wenya falls for the singer,

44
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,930
are we doing a buy-one-get-one-free?

45
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,720
Ladies, our store is having an anniversary event.

46
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:50,800
Show this flyer to get a 50% discount.

47
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,240
Check it out if you're interested.

48
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,000
Thanks.

49
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:55,760
Hey.

50
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:59,000
It says here that you can sign up for a competition.

51
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,930
I think you two should give it a try.

52
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:01,640
Competition?

53
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:02,700
What competition?

54
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:03,970
Look at this.

55
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:04,960
It says,

56
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:07,960
the most popular performer

57
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:11,000
can get the shop's treasured John Williams'

58
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,000
used guitar.

59
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:12,840
John?

60
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:15,400
This John Williams is Sister Wenya's

61
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,760
favorite guitarist.

62
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,920
I think if you can get this,

63
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:19,850
it will work out.

64
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:24,690
But I can't play the guitar.

65
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:27,160
You have me.

66
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:33,480
Good brother.

67
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:37,760
Good brother, pay me back the money you owe me for the flowers first.

68
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:38,480
All right.

69
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,480
Put it on my tab.

70
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:41,680
Here.

71
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,760
This is

72
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:52,200
50 for the flowers.

73
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:54,280
This is

74
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:56,040
25 for fixing the guitar.

75
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:00,560
This is 10 for the boxed meal.

76
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:03,120
All right, all right.

77
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,720
Stop showing them one by one.

78
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:05,720
I trust you.

79
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:06,480
How much in total?

80
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:07,680
Just give me a number.

81
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:08,960
It's

82
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:11,400
1,725.34 in total.

83
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,320
Uh, with inflation

84
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:14,840
and a 90% discount,

85
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,529
just give me 50,000.

86
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:21,800
Okay.

87
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:23,880
Then give me all the IOUs first,

88
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,490
and then write a new one.

89
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,240
Wow.

90
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:40,360
So handsome.

91
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:35,040
Oh my god.

92
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,400
Sister Wenya,

93
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:39,780
you're not asleep yet?

94
00:06:40,159 --> 00:06:41,760
What bad things have you done

95
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,060
to be scared like this?

96
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,280
No.

97
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:48,690
Just came back from working overtime.

98
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Oh.

99
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:54,360
Your boss called home today

100
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:56,900
and specially asked about your illness.

101
00:06:59,000 --> 00:06:59,600
Oh.

102
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,200
Ouch.

103
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:02,320
Ouch, yes.

104
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:03,520
I was a little...

105
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,640
My stomach hurt

106
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:05,320
and I just,

107
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:07,340
just came back from the hospital.

